NOTE:PROFESSIONAL PROFILE\n\nEducation: Chemical Engineering\, University of Pretoria; Bachelor's degree\, University of Arkansas.\n\nCareer History: Over 33 years of experience. Previously held positions at AgroFresh\, Tessara\, Ascendis Health\, Sanofi\, VaxServe\, and S&B. Currently Group CEO of Chill Beverages International.\n\nCompany Background: Chill Beverages was founded in 2001 in Stellenbosch with 4 staff and has grown to approximately 370 employees. Brand portfolio includes Score Energy Drink\, Fitch & Leedes Mixers\, Chateau Del Rei\, Bashew's\, and MiWater. In May 2024\, an AAA Fund-led consortium (including Alterra Capital\, Mineworkers Investment Company\, and Admaius Capital Partners) acquired a majority stake.\n\nAreas of Expertise: Beverage manufacturing; consumer goods; chemical engineering; operational leadership.\n\nSources:\nhttps://www.zoominfo.com/p/Jaco-Smit/2590728211\nhttps://www.chillbev.co.za/contact-us\nhttps://www.avca.africa/news-insights/member-news/alterra-capital-leads-acquisition-of-chill-beverages-with-aaa-fund/
